# Cursor Rules — Laravel 12 (DevDocs Blade Monolith)

## 0) Role & Output Style

- You are a senior Laravel 12 (PHP 8.2) full-stack engineer using Blade.
- Prefer clean, production-ready server-rendered code.
- Always explain briefly what you changed after code.
- Do not invent files that don't exist; if creating new files, list exact paths.
- Use web routes (not API routes).
- All responses must be actionable: include commands, file paths, and exact code.
- Prefer simplicity over over-engineering.

---

## 1) Project Principles

This is a **Laravel Blade monolith documentation platform**:

**Public Portal:** Browse published docs, hero search on homepage, view doc by slug (`/docs/{slug}`).

**User Portal:** Register/Login (session-based auth), Create/Edit/Delete docs, upload cover image, Publish/Unpublish.

- Only `published` docs are publicly visible.
- Users can only manage their own docs.
- Public URLs use slug: `/docs/{slug}`.
- All rendering is server-side using Blade.

---

## 2) Tech Choices

- Auth: Laravel built-in session authentication (NOT Sanctum)
- Routes: `routes/web.php`
- Views: Blade
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Interactivity: Alpine.js (only when necessary)
- Database: MySQL or PostgreSQL
- Storage: Laravel Storage (local disk for MVP)
- Content format: Markdown stored in DB (render safely in Blade)

---

## 3) Code Standards

**Use:** Form Requests, Policies, Service classes for complex logic (slug, file upload), Blade components.

**Do NOT use:** API Resources, JSON response formatting rules, Sanctum token logic.

- Controllers return `view()` responses.
- Redirect + session flash after form submission.
- Avoid fat controllers; use eager loading and `->select()` when listing docs.

---

## 4) Naming & Structure

**Models:** `User`, `Doc`, `Tag` (optional later).

**Controllers:** `app/Http/Controllers/Public/HomeController.php`, `DocPublicController.php`, `app/Http/Controllers/Dashboard/DocController.php`.

**Requests:** `app/Http/Requests/Doc/StoreDocRequest.php`, `UpdateDocRequest.php`.

**Policy:** `app/Policies/DocPolicy.php`.

**Views:** Layouts `resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php`, `dashboard.blade.php`. Public: `public/home.blade.php`, `public/docs/show.blade.php`. Dashboard: `dashboard/index.blade.php`, `dashboard/docs/index.blade.php`, `create.blade.php`, `edit.blade.php`. Component: `components/doc-card.blade.php`.

---

## 5) Database Rules (Docs table)

Fields: id, user_id (FK), title, slug (unique), excerpt (nullable), content (longText), cover_image_path (nullable), status enum `draft`|`published`, published_at (nullable), timestamps. Indexes: unique on slug, index on status, index on user_id.

---

## 6) Web Routes

**Public:** `GET /` → Home; `GET /docs/{slug}` → Doc detail (published only). Optional: `GET /ajax/docs?search=...` → JSON.

**Dashboard (auth):** `GET /dashboard`, `GET /dashboard/docs`, `GET /dashboard/docs/create`, `POST /dashboard/docs`, `GET /dashboard/docs/{doc}/edit`, `PUT /dashboard/docs/{doc}`, `DELETE /dashboard/docs/{doc}`, `POST /dashboard/docs/{doc}/publish`, `POST /dashboard/docs/{doc}/unpublish`.

---

## 7) Validation

**StoreDocRequest:** title required string min:5 max:160; content required min:30; excerpt nullable max:300; status required in:draft,published; cover_image nullable image max:2048. **UpdateDocRequest:** same fields, nullable; prevent slug change if status = published. Redirect back with errors on failure.

---

## 8) Slug Rules

Derive from title with `Str::slug`; ensure uniqueness (append -2, -3…); slug must NOT change after publish. Public route uses slug only.

---

## 9) File Upload

Store under `storage/app/public/docs/covers`; save path in DB; access via `asset('storage/...')` or `Storage::url()`; delete old cover when replacing; run `php artisan storage:link`.

---

## 10) Authorization

**DocPolicy:** User can update/delete/publish/unpublish only if `doc.user_id === auth()->id()`. Public controllers must enforce `status = published`.

---

## 11) Response Behavior (Blade)

- GET → `view()`; POST/PUT/DELETE → `redirect()->route()`.
- Session flash: `session()->flash('success', '...')`.
- All forms: `@csrf`; PUT/DELETE use `@method('PUT')` / `@method('DELETE')`.

---

## 12) Pagination

Use `->paginate(10)` and `{{ $docs->links() }}`; keep server-rendered.

---

## 13) Search

MVP: empty search → latest published; with search → filter by title and excerpt (LIKE), always `status = published`. AJAX: minimal JSON (id, title, slug).

---

## 14) Testing (Minimum)

Feature tests: register/login, create doc, public page shows only published, user cannot edit others' docs, slug uniqueness. Use factories.

---

## 15) Git & Environment

No hardcoded secrets; use `.env`; reversible migrations; do not commit storage files; `APP_DEBUG=false` in production.

---

## 16) When Unsure

Prefer server-rendered simplicity. Do NOT convert to API architecture. Avoid unnecessary packages. Keep logic clear and maintainable.

**Final mindset:** Clean Laravel Blade monolith — routes, controllers, Blade views, models, policies, storage in one app. No SPA, no separate frontend, no token-based auth. Simple and scalable.
